# Backend Rules - planning-poker-voting-service

## Scope

`planning-poker-voting-service` owns CMS/admin APIs, live sessions, participant web tokens, RBAC/team scope, scope boards, retrospectives, AI orchestration, rate limits and Telegram session finish alerts.

It must not call Jira REST directly; Jira access goes through `JIRA_SERVICE_URL` and the existing Jira service adapter.

## Read Before Changing

- Service boundaries: `../planning-poker-dev/docs/architecture/SERVICES.md`.
- Auth/RBAC: `../planning-poker-dev/docs/architecture/AUTH.md`.
- Data/storage: `../planning-poker-dev/docs/architecture/DATA.md`.
- API contracts: `../planning-poker-dev/docs/contracts/API.md`.
- Scope board: `../planning-poker-dev/docs/contracts/SCOPE-BOARD.md`.
- Sessions/voting: `../planning-poker-dev/docs/contracts/SESSIONS.md`.
- Development practices: `../planning-poker-dev/docs/development/GUIDE.md`.

## Implementation Rules

- Keep routers thin; put business logic in `app/domain`, `app/usecases` or existing service modules.
- Reuse existing ports/adapters, repositories, Pydantic models, error types, rate-limit helpers and test fixtures.
- Preserve API behavior unless a breaking change is explicitly required and documented.
- Every CMS endpoint needs authentication, permission check and team-scope/data access validation where applicable.
- Use existing optimistic concurrency semantics for session mutations; do not silently overwrite state.
- Reuse `app.state.http_session` for outbound HTTP; do not create per-request `ClientSession`.
- Do not log secrets, tokens, cookies, auth headers or sensitive user data.
- Preserve old snapshots/data on partial external dependency failure unless the contract explicitly says otherwise.

## Testing

- Changed business/domain/API logic requires pytest coverage in `tests/`.
- Auth/RBAC/team-scope changes require negative tests.
- Contract changes require tests for response shape, error path and frontend compatibility where relevant.
- Run `python3 -m pytest -q` before commit/push.

## Documentation

Update `../planning-poker-dev/docs/**` when endpoints, auth, storage, env vars, rate limits, scope/session behavior or integration contracts change.
